A Nyanga cop has been busted in connection with a kidnapping incident that took place in Delft, Cape Town last month. The arrest comes after another cop Constable Ngangaphila Somagaca (27) attached at Table Bay Harbour cop shop was also arrested in connection with the incident. According to Hawks spokesperson Warrant Officer Bonnie Nxumalo, the arrest emanates from a kidnapping that took place on Empress Tree Street in Thubelitsha in Delft on 22 January. Allegedly,  two victims were taken from their homes by four men and were held hostage in a house on Crescent Road, Phillipi East. “The suspects allegedly made off with the victim’s vehicle, a blue Ford Ranger bakkie which was later recovered at an informal settlement near Faure Drive. The victims who were seriously battered were rescued by the investigation team and were taken for medical attention,” said Nxumalo. Cops arrested Luvuyo Lwabi (33), Nicodemus Pasapanodya (32) and Andrew Soko (25) two days after the kidnapping incident and Somagaca was arrested a few days later and appeared in court on 3 February 2023 and were remanded in custody. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Nxumalo said the arrested cop is also Constable aged 35 attached to the Nyanga Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit (FCS). He is expected to appear in the Bellville Magistrates’ Court on 17 February 2023 for charges of kidnapping, robbery with aggravating circumstances, and assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. “The suspect was arrested by the Provincial Kidnapping Task Team consisting of the Hawks’ Serious Organised Crime Investigation, Provincial Organised Crime, and Crime Intelligence on Wednesday, 15 February 2023. They will join the suspect at court where they will be applying to be released on bail,” Nxumalo added.